There are 169656 associations in the replication file of which 155190 in cis and 14466

Variance explained

Using an independent replication allows unbiased estimate of phenotypic variance explained

The cumulative plot shows variance explained in various percentages of DNA methylation sites. 99 % of the cis associations explain less than 0.2094 and 99% of the trans associations explain less than 0.1552 of the variance.

What proportion of h2 is explained? To summarise this set probes with h2==0 to h2==1e-10 because this gives division errors. r2 for probes with h2==0 are set to 0.

  • There are 1927 CpGs with h2==0.

There are 2717 proportions above 1. These will be set to 1.
